lines.text: From: Waterloo Region Nurse Practitioner-Led Clinic
WATERLOO REGION NURSE PRACTITIONER LED CLINIC
123 Pioneer Drive, Unit B204, Kitchener N2P 243
Re: Adelina Marcu Jul 29, 1991 Age: 34 yr
Thank you for seeing this 34-year-old female, known to you, who is a new patient to our
practice. I am writing to re-refer her to your care for follow-up of her thyroid condition.
She was previously under your care several years ago for investigation of symptoms
Including hot flashes, which led to a workup for thyroid dysfunction. She recalls that her
blood work showed some significantly abnormal results and that Hashimoto's thyroiditis
was considered. She was advised to follow up with you but was lost to follow-up due to
personal circumstances. She is now eager to re-engage with her health and has specifically
requested to be referred back to your service for continuity of care.
Her current medications consist of over-the-counter supplements, including a
magnesium/zinc blend, vitamin C, and vitamin D 2000 IU daily. She has a significant
family history of hypothyroidism in both her mother and father.
Thank you for reassessing this pleasant patient and continuing her care.
